<%- include('_head', { title: 'Webhooks' }) %>

<h1>Webhooks</h1>
<p class="subtitle">Trigger the newsletter from other apps, or notify a service after each send.</p>

<% if (flash.saved)  { %><div class="alert alert-success">Saved.</div><% } %>
<% if (flash.error)  { %><div class="alert alert-error">Error: <%= flash.error %></div><% } %>

<!-- ── INCOMING ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="card" style="margin-bottom:24px;">
  <h3>Incoming — Trigger a send</h3>
  <p class="muted">POST to this URL from any automation tool (Home Assistant, Zapier, Make, Shortcuts…) to trigger an immediate newsletter send.</p>

  <% if (config.webhook_secret) { %>
    <div class="form-group" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <label>Webhook URL</label>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;">
        <code class="webhook-url"><%= protocol %>://<%= host %>/webhook/<%= config.webhook_secret %></code>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-ghost"
          onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText('<%= protocol %>://<%= host %>/webhook/<%= config.webhook_secret %>');this.textContent='Copied!';setTimeout(()=>this.textContent='Copy',2000)">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <p class="field-hint">Method: <code>POST</code> &nbsp;·&nbsp; No body or auth header needed — the secret is in the URL.</p>
    </div>
  <% } else { %>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:12px;">No secret generated yet. Click below to create one.</p>
  <% } %>

  <form method="POST" action="/setup/webhooks" style="margin-top:16px;">
    <input type="hidden" name="action" value="regenerate">
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-ghost">
      <%= config.webhook_secret ? 'Regenerate Secret' : 'Generate Secret' %>
    </button>
  </form>

  <% if (config.webhook_secret) { %>
    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <strong>Example:</strong><br>
      <code>curl -X POST "<%= protocol %>://<%= host %>/webhook/<%= config.webhook_secret %>"</code>
    </div>
  <% } %>
</div>

<!-- ── OUTGOING ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="card" style="margin-bottom:24px;">
  <h3>Outgoing — Notify after each send</h3>
  <p class="muted">After each successful newsletter send, Daily Schedule will POST a JSON payload to this URL. Leave blank to disable.</p>

  <form method="POST" action="/setup/webhooks" class="form" style="margin-top:16px;">
    <input type="hidden" name="action" value="save-outgoing">
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Notify URL <span class="hint">(Slack incoming webhook, Make scenario, etc.)</span></label>
      <input type="url" name="webhook_outgoing_url"
        value="<%= config.webhook_outgoing_url || '' %>"
        placeholder="https://hooks.slack.com/services/…">
    </div>
    <div class="callout" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <strong>Payload sent:</strong><br>
      <code>{"date":"2026-03-21","dateStr":"Saturday, March 21, 2026","status":"success","subject":"Daily Smith – …","sentTo":"family@example.com"}</code>
    </div>
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
    <% if (config.webhook_outgoing_url) { %>
      <span class="field-hint" style="margin-left:12px;">Currently set to: <strong><%= config.webhook_outgoing_url %></strong></span>
    <% } %>
  </form>
</div>

<!-- ── DISTRIBUTION ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="card">
  <h3>Distribution — Deliver newsletter via webhook</h3>
  <p class="muted">In addition to email, POST the full newsletter content to an endpoint on every send. Use this to push the newsletter to a custom display, Home Assistant dashboard, Discord bot, or any other integration.</p>

  <form method="POST" action="/setup/webhooks" class="form" style="margin-top:16px;">
    <input type="hidden" name="action" value="save-distribution">
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Distribution URL</label>
      <input type="url" name="webhook_distribution_url"
        value="<%= config.webhook_distribution_url || '' %>"
        placeholder="https://your-server.example.com/newsletter">
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Secret / Token <span class="hint">(optional — sent as <code>Authorization: Bearer …</code>)</span></label>
      <input type="text" name="webhook_distribution_secret"
        value="<%= config.webhook_distribution_secret || '' %>"
        placeholder="Leave blank if your endpoint needs no auth"
        autocomplete="off">
    </div>
    <div class="callout" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <strong>Payload sent:</strong><br>
      <code>{"date":"2026-03-21","dateStr":"Saturday, March 21, 2026","subject":"Daily Smith – …","familyName":"Smith","html":"&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;…"}</code>
      <p style="margin:8px 0 0;font-size:12px;">The <code>html</code> field contains the full email HTML — the same content that gets emailed to your family. Your endpoint can render it in an iframe, forward it to another service, or parse it however you like.</p>
    </div>
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
    <% if (config.webhook_distribution_url) { %>
      <span class="field-hint" style="margin-left:12px;">Currently delivering to: <strong><%= config.webhook_distribution_url %></strong></span>
    <% } %>
  </form>
</div>

<!-- ── IFTTT ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="card" style="margin-top:24px;">
  <h3>IFTTT — Email trigger</h3>
  <p class="muted">After each send, email <code>trigger@applet.ifttt.com</code> with a plain-text summary and the PDF attached. Set up an IFTTT applet using the <strong>Email</strong> trigger to forward it to a push notification, smart display, or any other service.</p>

  <form method="POST" action="/setup/webhooks" class="form" style="margin-top:16px;">
    <input type="hidden" name="action" value="save-ifttt">
    <div class="form-group">
      <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;cursor:pointer;">
        <input type="checkbox" name="ifttt_enabled" value="1" <%= config.ifttt_enabled === '1' ? 'checked' : '' %>>
        Enable IFTTT trigger email
      </label>
      <p class="field-hint">The trigger email is sent from your configured email account to <code>trigger@applet.ifttt.com</code> after every real send (not test sends).</p>
    </div>

    <details style="margin-bottom:20px;">
      <summary class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;">
        Step-by-step IFTTT setup
      </summary>
      <div style="margin-top:14px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;">
        <ol style="margin:0;padding-left:20px;">
          <li>Log in to <a href="https://ifttt.com" target="_blank">IFTTT</a> and click <strong>Create</strong>.</li>
          <li>For <strong>If This</strong>, choose the <strong>Email</strong> service → <strong>Send IFTTT an email</strong>.</li>
          <li>Connect the Email service — IFTTT will confirm the email address you use. <strong>That address must match the From address of your configured email account</strong> so IFTTT recognises the sender.</li>
          <li>For <strong>Then That</strong>, choose whatever action you like — e.g. <em>Notifications → Send a rich notification from the IFTTT app</em>, or <em>Google Drive → Add file from URL</em>.</li>
          <li>In the action, use IFTTT ingredients: <code>{{Subject}}</code> for the newsletter date, <code>{{Body}}</code> for the plain-text summary, and <code>{{AttachmentUrl}}</code> if a PDF was attached.</li>
          <li>Enable the toggle above and save. The trigger email will be sent after the next scheduled send.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </details>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <strong>Email format:</strong><br>
      <strong>To:</strong> <code>trigger@applet.ifttt.com</code><br>
      <strong>Subject:</strong> <code>{From Name} - {date of newsletter}</code> — e.g. <em>The Daily Smith - Wednesday May 7 2026</em><br>
      <strong>Body:</strong> Plain text — weather (condition, high/low in °F and °C, rain chance), clothing tip, and full schedule with times<br>
      <strong>Attachment:</strong> The newsletter PDF (available as <code>{{AttachmentUrl}}</code> in IFTTT)
    </div>

    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
  </form>
</div>

<div class="form-actions" style="margin-top:24px;">
  <a href="/setup" class="btn btn-ghost">Back to Dashboard</a>
</div>

<style>
.webhook-url {
  font-family: monospace;
  font-size: 13px;
  background: #f1ede4;
  padding: 6px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  word-break: break-all;
  flex: 1;
}
.callout {
  margin-top: 14px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  background: #eff6ff;
  border: 1px solid #bfdbfe;
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: #1e40af;
  line-height: 1.55;
}
.callout code {
  font-family: monospace;
  font-size: 12px;
  word-break: break-all;
}
</style>

<%- include('_foot') %>
